  "fun_facts": [
    "Derived from wine barrels where it crystallizes as 'wine diamonds' or 'wine crystals' during aging",
    "The main acid responsible for the characteristic tartness of grapes and wine",
    "Its name comes from the Medieval Latin 'tartarum' meaning 'wine cask sediment'",
    "Used by Louis Pasteur in 1847 to demonstrate molecular chirality (handedness), a landmark discovery in chemistry"
